textgroups.text: Go to a health center to check for and manage these conditions
A person with anemia does not have enough red cells in her blood. Red blood cells transport oxygen from our lungs to the rest of our body.
If our body does not get enough oxygen, it cannot work properly. Our cells will start to die.

textgroups.text: The high pressure can squeeze the vessels that carry blood from the mother to the baby.
Everything that the baby needs to grow is transported in blood, so if the blood cannot get through the vessels, then the baby cannot grow well.
A person with diabetes has too much sugar in their blood.
Women can develop diabetes during pregnancy.
Go to a health center to check for and manage these conditions
This can cause the baby to grow too large, and you might need a Cesarean section.

textgroups.text: Go to a health center to check for and manage these conditions
HIV and syphilis are transmitted by blood and sexual fluids. If the mother has HIV or syphilis, she can transmit it to the baby during birth.
The child will have HIV for its whole life. Syphilis can be cured, but it can cause serious disability in the baby if it’s not treated in time.

Plant medicine cannot treat or cure HIV.

textgroups.text: Over a long time, HIV destroys the defense system of your body. Your body becomes weak and can no longer fight off normal illnesses.
Syphilis can travel to your brain and organs and damage them, if it is not treated for a long time.
Tuberculosis is an infection in your lungs. It is spread through the air by coughing. It can be in your body for many years before making you sick.
A woman with tuberculosis is at higher risk for illness during pregnancy and miscarriages.
Go to a health center to check for and manage these conditions

textgroups.text: Bacteria are like tiny animals that can grow inside of our body and on our skin.

Our body has many defenses to get rid of bacteria: coughing, fever, vomiting, diarrhea.
